# Development Guidelines

- **Always practise test-driven development.** Write tests first, then implement until tests pass.
- **Use the brainstorming skill before adding new components.** Think through component/command/screen design before writing code.
- **Use systematic debugging when tests fail.** Diagnose root causes rather than guessing.
- **Run verification before claiming work is complete.** Ensure all tests pass and the code meets the spec.
{% if api_contract %}- Match the API Contract exactly for all API calls — endpoint paths, request schemas, and response shapes.
{% endif %}- Follow the tech stack and coding conventions specified in the Frontend Spec.
- Write meaningful test descriptions that document behavior.
{% if frontend_kind is defined and frontend_kind == "cli" %}- **Handle all external call failures graciously** — emit descriptive stderr messages and set a non-zero exit code; never dump raw tracebacks.
- **Validate inputs at the flag/argument level** with clear error messages.
{% else %}- **Implement error boundaries** at the surface (page / screen / window) level to prevent full-app crashes.
- **Handle all external call failures graciously** — show user-friendly error messages, never raw error objects or stack traces.
- **Every loading state must have a corresponding error state.** If data can be loading, it can also fail.
- **Form inputs must validate and show clear feedback** before submission.
- **Network failures should offer retry options** where appropriate.
{% endif %}

# Documentation Requirements

Maintain the following documentation files at the root of the project. Review the **entire file** each sprint — do not just append. Remove or update any sections describing features, components, or patterns that have changed or been removed.

## README.md
Must contain:
- Project overview (what it does, who it's for)
- Prerequisites and setup instructions
- How to install dependencies and run the app
- How to run the test suite
- Summary of key features implemented so far

## ARCHITECTURE.md
Must contain:
- High-level frontend architecture overview
- Component hierarchy and routing structure
- State management approach
- Key design decisions and trade-offs
- External dependencies and their purpose

## CLAUDE.md
Must contain:
- Project tech stack and framework versions
- Coding conventions and component patterns used in this codebase
- How to run tests and key test commands
- Key utilities, hooks, and shared modules with their locations
- State management patterns and API integration conventions
- Any project-specific rules that help Claude Code work effectively in this project

# Required Output

When you are done, you **must** end your session with a brief plain-text summary:
- Number of tests passing
- List of files created or modified
- Documentation files created or updated
- Any issues encountered

Even if the feature was already implemented, produce a summary confirming it.
